-- Wiedner Becomes European Commission Insurance and Pensions Chief
-- B y   C a r o l y n   B a n d e l
-- 2013-03-20T10:59:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-20/wiedner-becomes-european-commission-insurance-and-pensions-chief.html
Klaus Wiedner became chief of a
unit overseeing insurance and pensions at the European
Commission’s Internal Market and Services division.  Wiedner, from  Austria , took up the post two days ago and
replaces Karel van Hulle, who retired at the end of January,
according to his office at the Brussels-based commission, the
European Union’s executive arm.  He previously worked as head of a unit responsible for
enforcing public procurement law in the same division.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carolyn Bandel in Zurich at 
 cbandel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
